00:06:22.110 --> 00:06:24.940
You can see my Harvest?

00:06:29.950 --> 00:06:32.780
Hey, you can see them, right?!

00:06:32.780 --> 00:06:34.960
Yeah, it's called a Stand.

00:06:36.360 --> 00:06:38.480
I'm Josuke Higashikata.

00:06:38.480 --> 00:06:40.530
This is Okuyasu Nijimura.

00:06:41.430 --> 00:06:45.020
Friends! I've never had any before!

00:06:45.920 --> 00:06:49.780
My name is Shigekiyo Yangu.

00:06:49.780 --> 00:06:52.380
I'm a second-year at Budogaoka Middle School.

00:06:52.380 --> 00:06:54.180
I weigh 110 kilograms,

00:06:54.180 --> 00:06:58.440
and my Papa and Mama call me "Shigechi."

00:06:58.440 --> 00:07:01.280
"Shige-chan" turned into "Shigechi."

00:07:01.280 --> 00:07:04.190
My turtle I have at home is named Gonta.

00:07:05.020 --> 00:07:10.090
The other day, I was wondering 
if the 41 yen, 62 yen,

00:07:10.090 --> 00:07:13.420
and 150 yen stamps all tasted different,

00:07:13.420 --> 00:07:16.580
so I was licking them all, 
and Mama yelled at me.

00:07:16.580 --> 00:07:19.410
This is a picture of my Mama, 
who yelled at me.

00:07:19.410 --> 00:07:20.800
A picture...

00:07:20.800 --> 00:07:23.950
Wow, your mom's actually kinda hot.

00:07:23.950 --> 00:07:24.960
How strange.

00:07:24.960 --> 00:07:26.500
U-Um...

00:07:26.500 --> 00:07:29.480
So, you call these things "Harvest"?

00:07:29.480 --> 00:07:32.120
Did they really gather up all this?

00:07:32.120 --> 00:07:36.070
Yup. From ditches and underneath 
vending machines and things...

00:07:36.070 --> 00:07:38.180
But I'm not a thief.

00:07:38.180 --> 00:07:40.930
The officer at the police box said that

00:07:40.930 --> 00:07:45.150
I didn't have to turn in any 
change under a hundred yen.

00:07:45.150 --> 00:07:47.690
I hate bad things!

00:07:47.690 --> 00:07:50.070
That's not a bad thing at all!

00:07:50.070 --> 00:07:53.090
Actually, I think you're doing 
something great for society.

00:07:53.090 --> 00:07:54.600
Though it's not much,

00:07:54.600 --> 00:07:58.370
you're putting all of the forgotten 
change back into the Japanese economy.

00:07:58.370 --> 00:08:00.210
That's a great thing.

00:08:02.540 --> 00:08:05.770
Really? I'm great?

00:08:05.770 --> 00:08:09.510
Hey, do you think I'm a great person?

00:08:09.970 --> 00:08:12.480
It's what you'd call a blind spot for ideas.

00:08:12.480 --> 00:08:16.930
No one would do all this to get money.

00:08:16.930 --> 00:08:20.520
I'm jealous... You're smart.

00:08:20.520 --> 00:08:25.240
D-Did you just call me smart?

00:08:25.240 --> 00:08:29.140
N-No one's ever told me that before.

00:08:29.140 --> 00:08:31.730
I've picked up about 120,000 yen, but...

00:08:31.730 --> 00:08:33.860
120,000?!

00:08:33.860 --> 00:08:36.860
B-But that makes me even happier!

00:08:36.860 --> 00:08:38.940
A t-total of 120,000?!

00:08:38.940 --> 00:08:40.210
Aren't I a good boy?

00:08:40.210 --> 00:08:42.740
J-Just here in Morioh?

00:08:42.740 --> 00:08:46.910
Ayup! I don't go outside of Morioh.

00:08:46.910 --> 00:08:51.190
I might get lost and someone might kidnap me.

00:08:51.190 --> 00:08:55.120
