00:16:13.500 --> 00:16:14.990
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

00:16:21.750 --> 00:16:28.210
Oh, yeah. Here, Josuke, Okuyasu. 
Here's your share, 10,000 yen.

00:16:33.950 --> 00:16:36.800
Shigechi, what is this?

00:16:39.280 --> 00:16:44.640
We've got friendship, right? 
We're friends, right?

00:16:44.640 --> 00:16:46.310
Yeah, we are.

00:16:46.310 --> 00:16:50.380
So that's a token of our friendship.

00:16:51.990 --> 00:16:53.330
Hey, wait...

00:16:53.330 --> 00:16:55.970
This isn't what we promised, is it?

00:16:55.970 --> 00:16:59.870
You said okay to us getting half,
and you getting the other.

00:16:59.870 --> 00:17:04.410
Half of 61,500 yen is 30,750 exactly.

00:17:04.410 --> 00:17:08.090
R-Really? Did I say that?

00:17:08.090 --> 00:17:08.670
What?

00:17:08.670 --> 00:17:10.700
N-N-Not to mention...

00:17:10.700 --> 00:17:15.460
It w-was my H-Harvest's job 
to collect all of those.

00:17:15.460 --> 00:17:16.960
I did it all!

00:17:16.960 --> 00:17:20.850
Y-You two were just talking and did nothing.

00:17:20.850 --> 00:17:24.260
<i>And</i>, if Josuke hadn't come up with the idea,

00:17:24.260 --> 00:17:27.570
you never would have thought 
of gathering up all those!

00:17:27.570 --> 00:17:30.030
I would have eventually thought of it!

00:17:30.030 --> 00:17:31.990
I'm an awesome guy!

00:17:31.990 --> 00:17:36.410
Er... No, no... You never would have 
thought of it with that pea brain of yours!

00:17:38.030 --> 00:17:42.290
Hey, stop, Okuyasu.
Come here, fall back a sec.

00:17:43.840 --> 00:17:46.370
This is just great.

00:17:46.370 --> 00:17:48.580
Apparently he was fine with a few thousand,

00:17:48.580 --> 00:17:53.270
but once it went over ten thousand, 
he's much more hesitant to pay up.

00:17:55.400 --> 00:17:59.750
I don't think he means anything bad by it,
but since he's got the mind of a kid,

00:17:59.750 --> 00:18:03.190
no matter what we say,
he's gonna feel like we tricked him.

00:18:03.690 --> 00:18:07.270
We should be the adults here and let it be.

00:18:07.270 --> 00:18:11.070
We got 10,000 yen out of it, 
so let's call that good.

00:18:11.070 --> 00:18:14.430
I guess if you're okay with it, I won't argue...

00:18:14.430 --> 00:18:17.440
But this just pisses me off so much!

00:18:17.440 --> 00:18:19.610
Are you sure he's not taking advantage of us?

00:18:19.610 --> 00:18:22.990
No, Okuyasu, there's no point 
in fighting right now.

00:18:22.990 --> 00:18:27.570
We just need to teach Shigechi how 
adults actually make agreements.

00:18:27.570 --> 00:18:30.580
Oh, so you can make more money?

00:18:30.580 --> 00:18:32.710
You smug bastard...

00:18:33.680 --> 00:18:36.340
But that's what I love about you.

00:18:36.700 --> 00:18:40.080
All right, thanks. We'll gladly take this.

00:18:41.360 --> 00:18:42.850
Okuyasu.

00:18:42.850 --> 00:18:44.600
Are you thirsty?

00:18:44.600 --> 00:18:47.490
Is there anything you want to drink? I'll buy.

00:18:47.490 --> 00:18:49.450
You're going to buy it for me?

00:18:49.450 --> 00:18:52.360
Then... I want some Calpis Water.

00:18:52.360 --> 00:18:53.850
Then drink some.

00:18:57.400 --> 00:19:00.020
Ah! Hey! Why are you throwing those away?

00:19:00.020 --> 00:19:03.660
They're just worthless junk tickets, 
like for the year-end lottery.

00:19:03.660 --> 00:19:08.290
I told Shigechi to pick them up along 
with everything else earlier.

00:19:08.290 --> 00:19:11.220
